The paper deals with closure properties of languages under Boolean operations and concatenation, which is a fundamental topic in formal language theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the study of decidability and separation properties of language classes, which are also common themes in the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
